#encoding: utf-8

Feature: Temporal2 - Create Temporal Values from a String

@skip
  Scenario Outline: [1] Should parse date from string
    Given any graph
    When executing query:
      """
      RETURN date(<str>) AS result
      """
    Then the result should be, in any order:
      | result   |
      | <result> |
    And no side effects

    Examples:
      | str          | result       |
      | '2015-07-21' | '2015-07-21' |
      | '20150721'   | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-07'    | '2015-07-01' |
      | '201507'     | '2015-07-01' |
      | '2015-W30-2' | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015W302'   | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015-W30'   | '2015-07-20' |
      | '2015W30'    | '2015-07-20' |
      | '2015-202'   | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015202'    | '2015-07-21' |
      | '2015'       | '2015-01-01' |

